<title>USA: Chiron asks for Nasdaq halt for FDA review.</title>
<headline>Chiron asks for Nasdaq halt for FDA review.</headline>
<dateline>EMERYVILLE, Calif. 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Chiron Corp said Thursday it has asked Nasdaq for a trading halt of its stock while a U.S. Food and Drug Administration panel meets over its injection treatment for Lou Gherig's disease.</p>
<p>The company said it expects trading to resume after it announces the FDA panel's recommendation on its treatment, which is called Myotrophin. It has been developed by Chiron and its partner, Cephalon Inc.</p>
<p>The FDA's Peripheral and Central Nervous System Drugs Advisory Committee was to meet Thursday. A company spokeswoman said a recommendation was expected later in the afternoon.</p>
